children.subject: 184 is Graphics. Not sure what the connection is to ML/AI, unless you're talking about something like CV, which would be 194-26.

history.content:
For robotics, you should take EECS 106A/B., and probably EE 128. 192 is very mechatronics focused, which is certainly a worthwhile path in robotics, but definitely isn't used much in the ML/AI side of the field.

I was a MechE major and did an EECS minor with 188, 128, 106A/B, 192 and I'm now a PhD student in robotics (controls side). I don't use the material in 192 at all, and the course I most regret not taking is 126.

Currently an ME major interested in doubling. Not sure what EE classes might be good for robotics (taking 126 for probability, and would like to take 192). I know 188, 182 and 189 are good for ML/AI, but would love to hear more suggestions!
history.subject: Good Classes for robotics, ML/AI?
